misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that an array right shift task requires saving the last element, iterating backwards from the second-to-last element, copying the value from index (i-1) to index i, and finally placing the saved last element into the first position. This is the correct conceptual model for a single right circular shift.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no conceptual gap. The student's model of how arrays store data and how assignment operations overwrite memory locations sequentially is correct for this specific problem.
